The paper deals with the problem of sparse approximation over redundant dictionaries in complex cases, which involves complex measurement vectors, complex dictionaries, and complex additive white Gaussian noise. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a sufficient condition for exact recovery of sparse signals in complex cases, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization techniques, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-categories.
